President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring May 3 through May 9, 2020, as Public Service Recognition Week. The proclamation pays tribute to the dedication and hard work of federal, state, and local government employees in serving their fellow Americans. It highlights their efforts in responding to the coronavirus pandemic and ensuring the provision of necessary services, forging government-private sector partnerships, and supporting ongoing recovery efforts. The proclamation emphasizes the crucial role of public service employees in reopening the country, restarting the economy, and safeguarding American lives. The President commits to supporting these employees at all levels of government and calls upon Americans and government agencies to recognize and observe Public Service Recognition Week through appropriate programs and activities.